clusterRuntimeTable.name: clusterRuntimeTable

clusterRuntimeIndex.description: Unique value directed from ObjectName which is used as table index

clusterRuntimeParent.description: BEA-proprietary Parent object's identification, with syntax <type>:<name>

clusterRuntimeAliveServerCount.description: The current total number of alive servers in this cluster.

clusterRuntimeResendRequestsCount.name: clusterRuntimeResendRequestsCount
clusterRuntimeResendRequestsCount.description: The number of state-delta messages that had to be resent because a receiving server in the cluster missed a message.

clusterRuntimeFragmentsSentCount.description: The total number of multicast fragments sent from this server into the cluster.

clusterRuntimeFragmentsReceivedCount.name: clusterRuntimeFragmentsReceivedCount
clusterRuntimeFragmentsReceivedCount.description: The total number of multicast messages received on this server from the cluster.

clusterRuntimeMulticastMessagesLostCount.name: clusterRuntimeMulticastMessagesLostCount
clusterRuntimeMulticastMessagesLostCount.description: The total number of in-coming multicast messages that were lost according to this server.

clusterRuntimeServerNames.description: The names of the servers in the cluster.

clusterRuntimeSecondaryDistributionNames.description: Answer the names of the remote servers (e.g. myserver) of which the local server is hosting secondary objects. The name is appended with a number to indicate the number of secondaries hosted on behalf of that server.

clusterRuntimePrimaryCount.name: clusterRuntimePrimaryCount
clusterRuntimePrimaryCount.description: Answer the number of object that the local server hosts as primaries.

clusterRuntimeForeignFragmentsDroppedCou.name: clusterRuntimeForeignFragmentsDroppedCount
clusterRuntimeForeignFragmentsDroppedCou.description: Provides the number of fragments that originated in foreign domains or clusters which use the same multicast address. Answer the number of fragments that originated in foreign domains/cluster that use the same multicast address.

clusterRuntimeAsyncPrimaryCount.name: clusterRuntimeAsyncPrimaryCount
clusterRuntimeAsyncPrimaryCount.description: Provides the number of objects hosted by Aysnc Replication Manager on local server as primaries.

queryCacheRuntimeTotalCachedQueriesCount.description: Returns the count of the total number of query results for this EJB currently in the query cache.

queryCacheRuntimeCacheAccessCount.description: Returns the count of the number of accesses of the query cache for this EJB.

queryCacheRuntimeCacheHitCount.description: Returns the count of the number of cache hits of the query cache for this EJB.

queryCacheRuntimeCacheMissByBeanEviction.description: Returns the count of the number of cache misses of the query cache for this EJB because corresponding beans were not found in the entity cache.

queryCacheRuntimeCacheMissByRelatedQuery.description: Returns the count of the number of cache misses of the query cache for this EJB because a related query was not found in another EJB query cache.

queryCacheRuntimeCacheMissByDependentQue.description: Returns the count of the number of cache misses of the query cache for this EJB because a dependent query was not found in another EJB query cache.

serverRuntimeSSLListenPortEnabled.description: Return if the default lSSListenPort is enabled on the server

serverRuntimeRestartRequired.name: serverRuntimeRestartRequired
serverRuntimeRestartRequired.description: Indicates whether the server must be restarted in order to activate configuration changes.

serverRuntimeServerClasspath.name: serverRuntimeServerClasspath
serverRuntimeServerClasspath.description: Get the classpath for this server including domain/lib contents that are automatically picked up and appended to the classpath.

serverRuntimeCurrentMachine.name: serverRuntimeCurrentMachine
serverRuntimeCurrentMachine.description: Return the machine on which the server is running. This will be different from the configuration if the server gets migrated automatically. * @return Machine on which server is running.

serverRuntimeAdministrationURL.name: serverRuntimeAdministrationURL
serverRuntimeAdministrationURL.description: The URL that the server and its clients use for administrative connections. If no administration channel is enabled, then this method returns the URL for connections through the default channel. If the default channel is de-activated, this method returns the URL for a secure channel. If no secure channel is enabled, the method returns null. The returned URL will be consistent with dynamic channel updates.

serverRuntimeDefaultURL.name: serverRuntimeDefaultURL
serverRuntimeDefaultURL.description: The URL that clients use to connect to this server's default network channel. The returned value indicates the default protocol, listen address and listen port: protocol://listen-address:listen-port Note: The default protocol, listen address and listen port are persisted in the domain's config.xml file, however when a server instance is started, command-line options can override these persisted values. This getDefaultURL method returns the URL values that are currently being used, not necessarily the values that are specified in config.xml. The returned URL will be consistent with dynamic channel updates.

serverRuntimeStateVal.name: serverRuntimeStateVal
serverRuntimeStateVal.description: Returns current state of the server as in integer..

serverRuntimeCurrentDirectory.name: serverRuntimeCurrentDirectory
serverRuntimeCurrentDirectory.description: The absolute path of the directory from which the server was started. This may be used in conjunction with other relative paths in ServerMBean to compute full paths.

serverLifeCycleRuntimeTable.name: serverLifeCycleRuntimeTable
serverLifeCycleRuntimeTable.description: Provides values for Runtime server life cycle

serverLifeCycleRuntimeIndex.description: Unique value directed from ObjectName which is used as table index

serverLifeCycleRuntimeNodeManagerRestart.name: serverLifeCycleRuntimeNodeManagerRestartCount
serverLifeCycleRuntimeNodeManagerRestart.description: Number of times the server has been restarted using the NodeManager since creation. The first start does not count. The count is valid only if the NodeManager is used to start and restart the server everytime.

manReplicationRuntimeIndex.name: manReplicationRuntimeIndex
manReplicationRuntimeIndex.description: Unique value directed from ObjectName which is used as table index

manReplicationRuntimeParent.name: manReplicationRuntimeParent
manReplicationRuntimeParent.description: BEA-proprietary Parent object's identification, with syntax <type>:<name>

manReplicationRuntimeSecondaryServerName.name: manReplicationRuntimeSecondaryServerName

manReplicationRuntimeSecondaryServerDeta.name: manReplicationRuntimeSecondaryServerDetails
manReplicationRuntimeSecondaryServerDeta.description: Returns the detailed information about the secondary server.

manReplicationRuntimePrimaryCount.name: manReplicationRuntimePrimaryCount
manReplicationRuntimePrimaryCount.description: Returns the number of object that the local server hosts as primaries.

manReplicationRuntimeSecondaryCount.name: manReplicationRuntimeSecondaryCount
manReplicationRuntimeSecondaryCount.description: Returns the number of object that the local server hosts as secondaries.

manReplicationRuntimeRemoteClusterReacha.name: manReplicationRuntimeRemoteClusterReachable
manReplicationRuntimeRemoteClusterReacha.description: Returns true if the remote cluster is reachable.

maxThreadsConstraintRuntimeIndex.description: Unique value directed from ObjectName which is used as table index

maxThreadsConstraintRuntimeParent.name: maxThreadsConstraintRuntimeParent
maxThreadsConstraintRuntimeParent.description: BEA-proprietary Parent object's identification, with syntax <type>:<name>

maxThreadsConstraintRuntimeExecutingRequ.name: maxThreadsConstraintRuntimeExecutingRequests
maxThreadsConstraintRuntimeExecutingRequ.description: Returns the Number of requests that are currently executing.

maxThreadsConstraintRuntimeDeferredReque.name: maxThreadsConstraintRuntimeDeferredRequests
maxThreadsConstraintRuntimeDeferredReque.description: Returns the umber of requests that are denied a thread for execution because the constraint is exceeded.

minThreadsConstraintRuntimeTable.name: minThreadsConstraintRuntimeTable
minThreadsConstraintRuntimeTable.description: Provides values for Min Threads Constraints for the server

minThreadsConstraintRuntimeIndex.name: minThreadsConstraintRuntimeIndex
minThreadsConstraintRuntimeIndex.description: Unique value directed from ObjectName which is used as table index

minThreadsConstraintRuntimeParent.name: minThreadsConstraintRuntimeParent
minThreadsConstraintRuntimeParent.description: BEA-proprietary Parent object's identification, with syntax <type>:<name>

minThreadsConstraintRuntimeCompletedRequ.name: minThreadsConstraintRuntimeCompletedRequests
minThreadsConstraintRuntimeCompletedRequ.description: Returns the Number of requests that have completed executing.

minThreadsConstraintRuntimePendingReques.name: minThreadsConstraintRuntimePendingRequests
minThreadsConstraintRuntimePendingReques.description: Returns the Number of requests that are waiting for an available thread.

minThreadsConstraintRuntimeExecutingRequ.name: minThreadsConstraintRuntimeExecutingRequests
minThreadsConstraintRuntimeExecutingRequ.description: Returns the Number of requests that are currently executing.

minThreadsConstraintRuntimeOutOfOrderExe.name: minThreadsConstraintRuntimeOutOfOrderExecutionCount
minThreadsConstraintRuntimeOutOfOrderExe.description: Returns the Number of requests executed out of turn to satisfy this constraint.

minThreadsConstraintRuntimeMustRunCount.name: minThreadsConstraintRuntimeMustRunCount
minThreadsConstraintRuntimeMustRunCount.description: Returns the Number of requests that must be executed to satisfy the constraint.

minThreadsConstraintRuntimeMaxWaitTime.name: minThreadsConstraintRuntimeMaxWaitTime
minThreadsConstraintRuntimeMaxWaitTime.description: Returns the max time a request had to wait for a thread. Only requests whose execution is needed to satisfy the constraint are considered.

minThreadsConstraintRuntimeCurrentWaitTi.name: minThreadsConstraintRuntimeCurrentWaitTime
minThreadsConstraintRuntimeCurrentWaitTi.description: Returns the last measured time a request had to wait for a thread. Only requests whose execution is needed to satisfy the constraint are considered.

requestClassRuntimeTable.name: requestClassRuntimeTable
requestClassRuntimeTable.description: Presents runtime information about RequestClasses. A request class represents a class of work. Work using the same request class shares the same priority

requestClassRuntimeIndex.name: requestClassRuntimeIndex
requestClassRuntimeIndex.description: Unique value directed from ObjectName which is used as table index

requestClassRuntimeParent.name: requestClassRuntimeParent
requestClassRuntimeParent.description: BEA-proprietary Parent object's identification, with syntax <type>:<name>

requestClassRuntimeCompletedCount.name: requestClassRuntimeCompletedCount
requestClassRuntimeCompletedCount.description: Returns the Total number of completions since server start.

requestClassRuntimeTotalThreadUse.name: requestClassRuntimeTotalThreadUse
requestClassRuntimeTotalThreadUse.description: Returns the Total amount of thread use time in millisec's used by the request class since server start.

requestClassRuntimePendingRequestCount.name: requestClassRuntimePendingRequestCount
requestClassRuntimePendingRequestCount.description: Returns the Number of requests waiting for a thread to become available.

requestClassRuntimeVirtualTimeIncrement.name: requestClassRuntimeVirtualTimeIncrement
requestClassRuntimeVirtualTimeIncrement.description: Returns the Current priority of the request class. The priority is relative to other request class priorities. The priority is calculated dynamically frequently and can change.

requestClassRuntimeRequestClassType.name: requestClassRuntimeRequestClassType
requestClassRuntimeRequestClassType.description: Returns the type of RequestClass, either FIR_SHARE or RESPONSE_TIME.

requestClassRuntimeDeltaRepeat.name: requestClassRuntimeDeltaRepeat
requestClassRuntimeDeltaRepeat.description: Undocumented attribute that exposes a value used in determining priority

requestClassRuntimeDeltaFirst.name: requestClassRuntimeDeltaFirst
requestClassRuntimeDeltaFirst.description: Undocumented attribute that exposes a value used in determining priority

requestClassRuntimeThreadUseSquares.name: requestClassRuntimeThreadUseSquares
requestClassRuntimeThreadUseSquares.description: Undocumented attribute that exposes a value used in determining priority

requestClassRuntimeMyLast.name: requestClassRuntimeMyLast
requestClassRuntimeMyLast.description: Undocumented attribute that exposes a value used in determining priority

requestClassRuntimeInterval.name: requestClassRuntimeInterval
requestClassRuntimeInterval.description: Undocumented attribute that exposes a value used in determining priority. This attribute is applicable only for ResponseTimeRequestClass. -1 is returned for FairShareRequestClasses.

serverChannelRuntimeTable.name: serverChannelRuntimeTable
serverChannelRuntimeTable.description: Presents Runtime information for NetworkAccessPoints or Channels.

serverChannelRuntimeIndex.name: serverChannelRuntimeIndex
serverChannelRuntimeIndex.description: Unique value directed from ObjectName which is used as table index

serverChannelRuntimeParent.name: serverChannelRuntimeParent
serverChannelRuntimeParent.description: BEA-proprietary Parent object's identification, with syntax <type>:<name>

serverChannelRuntimeBytesReceivedCount.name: serverChannelRuntimeBytesReceivedCount
serverChannelRuntimeBytesReceivedCount.description: Returns the total number of bytes received on this channel.

serverChannelRuntimeBytesSentCount.name: serverChannelRuntimeBytesSentCount
serverChannelRuntimeBytesSentCount.description: Returns the total number of bytes sent on this channel.

serverChannelRuntimeChannelName.name: serverChannelRuntimeChannelName
serverChannelRuntimeChannelName.description: Returns the channel name of this channel.

serverChannelRuntimeConnectionsCount.name: serverChannelRuntimeConnectionsCount
serverChannelRuntimeConnectionsCount.description: Returns the number of active connections and sockets associated with this channel.

serverChannelRuntimeAcceptCount.name: serverChannelRuntimeAcceptCount
serverChannelRuntimeAcceptCount.description: Returns the number of sockets that have been accepted on this channel. This includes sockets both past and present so gives a good idea of the connection rate to the server.

serverChannelRuntimeMessagesReceivedCoun.name: serverChannelRuntimeMessagesReceivedCount
serverChannelRuntimeMessagesReceivedCoun.description: Returns the number of messages received on this channel.

serverChannelRuntimeMessagesSentCount.name: serverChannelRuntimeMessagesSentCount
serverChannelRuntimeMessagesSentCount.description: Returns the number of messages sent on this channel.

serverChannelRuntimePublicURL.name: serverChannelRuntimePublicURL
serverChannelRuntimePublicURL.description: Returns the physical URL that this channel is listening on.

threadPoolRuntimeTable.name: threadPoolRuntimeTable
threadPoolRuntimeTable.description: Presents Runtime information to monitor the self-tuning queue.

threadPoolRuntimeIndex.name: threadPoolRuntimeIndex
threadPoolRuntimeIndex.description: Unique value directed from ObjectName which is used as table index

threadPoolRuntimeParent.name: threadPoolRuntimeParent
threadPoolRuntimeParent.description: BEA-proprietary Parent object's identification, with syntax <type>:<name>

threadPoolRuntimeExecuteThreadTotalCount.name: threadPoolRuntimeExecuteThreadTotalCount
threadPoolRuntimeExecuteThreadTotalCount.description: Returns the total number of threads in the pool.

threadPoolRuntimeExecuteThreadIdleCount.name: threadPoolRuntimeExecuteThreadIdleCount
threadPoolRuntimeExecuteThreadIdleCount.description: Returns the number of idle threads in the pool.

threadPoolRuntimeQueueLength.name: threadPoolRuntimeQueueLength
threadPoolRuntimeQueueLength.description: Returns the number of pending requests in the priority queue. This is the total of internal system requests and user requests.

threadPoolRuntimePendingUserRequestCount.name: threadPoolRuntimePendingUserRequestCount
threadPoolRuntimePendingUserRequestCount.description: Returns the number of pending user requests in the priority queue. The priority queue contains requests from internal subsystems and users. This is just the count of all user requests.

threadPoolRuntimeSharedCapacityForWorkMa.name: threadPoolRuntimeSharedCapacityForWorkManagers
threadPoolRuntimeSharedCapacityForWorkMa.description: Returns the maximum amount of requests that can be accepted in the priority qeueue.

threadPoolRuntimeCompletedRequestCount.name: threadPoolRuntimeCompletedRequestCount
threadPoolRuntimeCompletedRequestCount.description: Returns the number of completed requests in the priority queue.

threadPoolRuntimeHoggingThreadCount.name: threadPoolRuntimeHoggingThreadCount
threadPoolRuntimeHoggingThreadCount.description: Returns the threads that are being hogged by a request right now. These threads will either be declared as stuck after the configured timeout or will return to the pool before that. The self-tuning mechanism will backfill if necessary.

threadPoolRuntimeStandbyThreadCount.name: threadPoolRuntimeStandbyThreadCount
threadPoolRuntimeStandbyThreadCount.description: Returns the number of threads in the standby pool. Surplus threads that are not needed to handle the present work load are designated as standby and added to the standby pool. These threads are activated when more threads are needed.

threadPoolRuntimeThroughput.name: threadPoolRuntimeThroughput
threadPoolRuntimeThroughput.description: Returns the mean number of requests completed per second.

threadPoolRuntimeMinThreadsConstraintsPe.name: threadPoolRuntimeMinThreadsConstraintsPending
threadPoolRuntimeMinThreadsConstraintsPe.description: Returns the Number of requests that should be executed now to satisfy the min threads requirement.

threadPoolRuntimeMinThreadsConstraintsCo.name: threadPoolRuntimeMinThreadsConstraintsCompleted
threadPoolRuntimeMinThreadsConstraintsCo.description: Returns the Number of requests with min threads constraint picked up out of order for execution immediately since their min threads requirement was not met. This does not include the case where threads are idle during schedule.

threadPoolRuntimeSuspended.name: threadPoolRuntimeSuspended
threadPoolRuntimeSuspended.description: Returns the Indicates if the RequestManager is suspended. A suspended manager will not dequeue work and dispatch threads till it is resumed

workManagerRuntimeTable.name: workManagerRuntimeTable

workManagerRuntimeParent.description: BEA-proprietary Parent object's identification, with syntax <type>:<name>

workManagerRuntimeModuleName.name: workManagerRuntimeModuleName
workManagerRuntimeModuleName.description: Returns the name of the module this WorkManager is associated with.

workManagerRuntimePendingRequests.name: workManagerRuntimePendingRequests
workManagerRuntimePendingRequests.description: Returns the number of waiting requests in the queue.

workManagerRuntimeCompletedRequests.name: workManagerRuntimeCompletedRequests
workManagerRuntimeCompletedRequests.description: Returns the number of requests that have been processed.

workManagerRuntimeStuckThreadCount.name: workManagerRuntimeStuckThreadCount
workManagerRuntimeStuckThreadCount.description: The number of thread that are considers stuck on the basis of any stuck thread constraints.

serverSecurityRuntimeParent.description: BEA-proprietary Parent object's identification, with syntax <type>:<name>

serverSecurityRuntimeJACCEnabled.name: serverSecurityRuntimeJACCEnabled
serverSecurityRuntimeJACCEnabled.description: Indicates whether JACC (Java Authorization Contract for Containers) was enabled on the commandline for the jvm hosting this server.

userLockoutManagerRuntimeTable.name: userLockoutManagerRuntimeTable
userLockoutManagerRuntimeTable.description: This table is used for monitoring per-Security Realm user lockout information.

userLockoutManagerRuntimeIndex.name: userLockoutManagerRuntimeIndex
userLockoutManagerRuntimeIndex.description: Unique value directed from ObjectName which is used as table index

userLockoutManagerRuntimeParent.name: userLockoutManagerRuntimeParent
userLockoutManagerRuntimeParent.description: BEA-proprietary Parent object's identification, with syntax <type>:<name>

userLockoutManagerRuntimeUserLockoutTota.name: userLockoutManagerRuntimeUserLockoutTotalCount
userLockoutManagerRuntimeUserLockoutTota.description: Returns the number of user lockouts that have occured since this server has been started.

userLockoutManagerRuntimeInvalidLoginAtt.name: userLockoutManagerRuntimeInvalidLoginAttemptsTotalCount
userLockoutManagerRuntimeInvalidLoginAtt.description: Returns the number of invalid logins attempted since this server has been started and lockouts have been enabled.

userLockoutManagerRuntimeLoginAttemptsWh.name: userLockoutManagerRuntimeLoginAttemptsWhileLockedTotalCount
userLockoutManagerRuntimeLoginAttemptsWh.description: Returns the number of invalid logins attempted since this server has been started and lockouts have been enabled.

userLockoutManagerRuntimeInvalidLoginUse.name: userLockoutManagerRuntimeInvalidLoginUsersHighCount
userLockoutManagerRuntimeInvalidLoginUse.description: Returns the highest number of users with concurrent unexpired or uncleared invalid login attempts.

userLockoutManagerRuntimeUnlockedUsersTo.name: userLockoutManagerRuntimeUnlockedUsersTotalCount
userLockoutManagerRuntimeUnlockedUsersTo.description: Returns the number times users have been unlocked since this server has been started.

userLockoutManagerRuntimeLockedUsersCurr.name: userLockoutManagerRuntimeLockedUsersCurrentCount
userLockoutManagerRuntimeLockedUsersCurr.description: Returns the number of users that are currently locked out of this server.

servletRuntimeIndex.name: servletRuntimeIndex
servletRuntimeIndex.description: Unique value directed from ObjectName which is used as table index

servletRuntimeParent.name: servletRuntimeParent
servletRuntimeParent.description: BEA-proprietary Parent object's identification, with syntax <type>:<name>

servletRuntimeReloadTotalCount.name: servletRuntimeReloadTotalCount
servletRuntimeReloadTotalCount.description: The total number of times the servelet has been reloaded.

servletRuntimeInvocationTotalCount.name: servletRuntimeInvocationTotalCount
servletRuntimeInvocationTotalCount.description: The total number of times the servelet has been invoked.

servletRuntimePoolMaxCapacity.name: servletRuntimePoolMaxCapacity
servletRuntimePoolMaxCapacity.description: The maximum capacity of this servlet for single thread model servlets.

servletRuntimeExecutionTimeTotal.name: servletRuntimeExecutionTimeTotal
servletRuntimeExecutionTimeTotal.description: The amount of time all invocations of the servlet has executed since created.

servletRuntimeExecutionTimeHigh.name: servletRuntimeExecutionTimeHigh
servletRuntimeExecutionTimeHigh.description: The amount of time the single longest invocation of the servlet has executed since created.

servletRuntimeExecutionTimeLow.name: servletRuntimeExecutionTimeLow
servletRuntimeExecutionTimeLow.description: The amount of time the single shortest invocation of the servlet has executed since created.

servletRuntimeExecutionTimeAverage.name: servletRuntimeExecutionTimeAverage
servletRuntimeExecutionTimeAverage.description: The average amount of time all invocations of the servlet have executed since created.

servletSessionRuntimeTable.name: servletSessionRuntimeTable
servletSessionRuntimeTable.description: This table is used for monitoring a WebLogic servlet session within a WebLogic server.

servletSessionRuntimeIndex.description: Unique value directed from ObjectName which is used as table index

taskRuntimeIndex.description: Unique value directed from ObjectName which is used as table index

taskRuntimeParent.name: taskRuntimeParent
taskRuntimeParent.description: BEA-proprietary Parent object's identification, with syntax <type>:<name>

taskRuntimeBeginTime.name: taskRuntimeBeginTime
taskRuntimeBeginTime.description: Returns the time at which this task was started.

taskRuntimeDescription.name: taskRuntimeDescription
taskRuntimeDescription.description: Returns a short, arbitrary String describing the nature of this task, e.g. 'Starting MyServer..

taskRuntimeEndTime.name: taskRuntimeEndTime
taskRuntimeEndTime.description: Returns the time at which this task was completed. Returns -1 if the task is currently running.

taskRuntimeStatus.name: taskRuntimeStatus
taskRuntimeStatus.description: eturns a short, arbitrary String describing the status of this Task, e.g. 'Starting Server', 'Completed', 'Failed'.

taskRuntimeRunning.name: taskRuntimeRunning
taskRuntimeRunning.description: Returns true if the Task is still running.

taskRuntimeSystemTask.name: taskRuntimeSystemTask
taskRuntimeSystemTask.description: Indicates this task was initiated by the server.

transactionNameRuntimeTable.name: transactionNameRuntimeTable
transactionNameRuntimeTable.description: This table represents runtime statistics for a transaction name category.

transactionNameRuntimeIndex.description: Unique value directed from ObjectName which is used as table index

transactionNameRuntimeParent.name: transactionNameRuntimeParent
transactionNameRuntimeParent.description: BEA-proprietary Parent object's identification, with syntax <type>:<name>

transactionNameRuntimeTransactionTotalCo.description: The total number of transactions processed. This total includes all committed, rolled back and heuristic transaction completions.

transactionNameRuntimeTransactionRolledB.name: transactionNameRuntimeTransactionRolledBackTotalCount
transactionNameRuntimeTransactionRolledB.description: The number of transactions that were rolled back.

transactionNameRuntimeTransactionHeurist.name: transactionNameRuntimeTransactionHeuristicsTotalCount
transactionNameRuntimeTransactionHeurist.description: The number of transactions that completed with a heuristic status.

transactionNameRuntimeTransactionRolledB.name: transactionNameRuntimeTransactionRolledBackResourceTotalCount
transactionNameRuntimeTransactionRolledB.description: The number of transactions that were rolled back due to a resource error.

transactionNameRuntimeTransactionRolledB.name: transactionNameRuntimeTransactionRolledBackAppTotalCount
transactionNameRuntimeTransactionRolledB.description: The number of transactions that were rolled back due to an application error.

transactionNameRuntimeTransactionRolledB.name: transactionNameRuntimeTransactionRolledBackSystemTotalCount
transactionNameRuntimeTransactionRolledB.description: The number of transactions that were rolled back due to an internal system error.

transactionNameRuntimeSecondsActiveTotal.name: transactionNameRuntimeSecondsActiveTotalCount
transactionNameRuntimeSecondsActiveTotal.description: The total number of seconds for all committed transactions.

transactionNameRuntimeTransactionRolledB.name: transactionNameRuntimeTransactionRolledBackTimeoutTotalCount
transactionNameRuntimeTransactionRolledB.description: The total number of seconds for all committed transactions.

transactionNameRuntimeTransactionAbandon.name: transactionNameRuntimeTransactionAbandonedTotalCount
transactionNameRuntimeTransactionAbandon.description: The total number of transactions that were abandoned since the server was started.

transactionResourceRuntimeTable.name: transactionResourceRuntimeTable
transactionResourceRuntimeTable.description: This table represents runtime statistics for a transactional resource.

transactionResourceRuntimeIndex.name: transactionResourceRuntimeIndex
transactionResourceRuntimeIndex.description: Unique value directed from ObjectName which is used as table index

transactionResourceRuntimeParent.name: transactionResourceRuntimeParent
transactionResourceRuntimeParent.description: BEA-proprietary Parent object's identification, with syntax <type>:<name>

transactionResourceRuntimeTransactionTot.name: transactionResourceRuntimeTransactionTotalCount
transactionResourceRuntimeTransactionTot.description: The total number of transactions processed. This total includes all committed, rolled back and heuristic transaction completions.

transactionResourceRuntimeTransactionRol.name: transactionResourceRuntimeTransactionRolledBackTotalCount
transactionResourceRuntimeTransactionRol.description: The number of transactions that were rolled back.

transactionResourceRuntimeTransactionHeu.name: transactionResourceRuntimeTransactionHeuristicsTotalCount
transactionResourceRuntimeTransactionHeu.description: The number of transactions that completed with a heuristic status.

transactionResourceRuntimeTransactionHeu.name: transactionResourceRuntimeTransactionHeuristicCommitTotalCount
transactionResourceRuntimeTransactionHeu.description: The number of transactions for which this resource has returned a heuristic commit decision.

transactionResourceRuntimeTransactionHeu.name: transactionResourceRuntimeTransactionHeuristicRollbackTotalCount
transactionResourceRuntimeTransactionHeu.description: The number of transactions for which this resource has returned a heuristic rollback decision.

transactionResourceRuntimeTransactionHeu.name: transactionResourceRuntimeTransactionHeuristicMixedTotalCount
transactionResourceRuntimeTransactionHeu.description: The number of transactions for which this resource has reported a heuristic mixed decision.

transactionResourceRuntimeTransactionHeu.name: transactionResourceRuntimeTransactionHeuristicHazardTotalCount
transactionResourceRuntimeTransactionHeu.description: The number of transactions for which this resource has reported a heuristic hazard decision.

webAppComponentRuntimeTable.name: webAppComponentRuntimeTable
webAppComponentRuntimeTable.description: This table describes a servlet component (servlet context).

webAppComponentRuntimeIndex.name: webAppComponentRuntimeIndex
webAppComponentRuntimeIndex.description: Unique value directed from ObjectName which is used as table index

webAppComponentRuntimeParent.name: webAppComponentRuntimeParent
webAppComponentRuntimeParent.description: BEA-proprietary Parent object's identification, with syntax <type>:<name>

webAppComponentRuntimeSourceInfo.name: webAppComponentRuntimeSourceInfo
webAppComponentRuntimeSourceInfo.description: Return an informative string about the component's source.

webAppComponentRuntimeServletSessions.name: webAppComponentRuntimeServletSessions
webAppComponentRuntimeServletSessions.description: Return the number of elements of the array of ServletRuntimeMBeans associated with this component

webAppComponentRuntimeServlets.name: webAppComponentRuntimeServlets
webAppComponentRuntimeServlets.description: Return an array of ServletRuntimeMBeans associated with this component

webAppComponentRuntimeOpenSessionsCurren.name: webAppComponentRuntimeOpenSessionsCurrentCount
webAppComponentRuntimeOpenSessionsCurren.description: The current total number of open sessions in this component.

webAppComponentRuntimeOpenSessionsHighCo.name: webAppComponentRuntimeOpenSessionsHighCount
webAppComponentRuntimeOpenSessionsHighCo.description: The high water mark of the total number of open sessions in this server. The count starts at zero each time the server is activated.

webAppComponentRuntimeSessionsOpenedTota.name: webAppComponentRuntimeSessionsOpenedTotalCount
webAppComponentRuntimeSessionsOpenedTota.description: The total number of sessions opened in this server.

webAppComponentRuntimeSingleThreadedServ.name: webAppComponentRuntimeSingleThreadedServletPoolSize
webAppComponentRuntimeSingleThreadedServ.description: Provides the single threaded servlet pool size as it is configured in weblogic.xml.

webAppComponentRuntimeJSPVerbose.name: webAppComponentRuntimeJSPVerbose
webAppComponentRuntimeJSPVerbose.description: Provides the jsp's verbose parameter value as it is configured in weblogic.xml.

webAppComponentRuntimeIndexDirectoryEnab.name: webAppComponentRuntimeIndexDirectoryEnabled
webAppComponentRuntimeIndexDirectoryEnab.description: Provides the directory indexing indicator as it is configured in weblogic.xml.

webAppComponentRuntimeModuleId.name: webAppComponentRuntimeModuleId
webAppComponentRuntimeModuleId.description: Returns the identifier for this Component. The identifier is unique within the application. Typical modules will use the URI for their id. Web Modules will return their context-root since the web-uri may not be unique within an EAR.

webAppComponentRuntimeJSPDebug.name: webAppComponentRuntimeJSPDebug
webAppComponentRuntimeJSPDebug.description: Provides the jsp's debug/linenumbers parameter value as it is configured in weblogic.xml.

webAppComponentRuntimeSessionCookieName.name: webAppComponentRuntimeSessionCookieName
webAppComponentRuntimeSessionCookieName.description: By default, all applications on WebLogic Server specify 'JSESSIONID' as the cookie name. To provide a more specific name, edit your application's weblogic.xml deployment descriptor.

webAppComponentRuntimeSessionCookieDomai.name: webAppComponentRuntimeSessionCookieDomain
webAppComponentRuntimeSessionCookieDomai.description: By default, clients can return cookies only to the server that issued the cookie. You can change this default behavior by editing your application's weblogic.xml deployment descriptor. For more information, see Cookie.setDomain() in the Servlet specification from Sun Microsystems.

webAppComponentRuntimeFilterDispatchedRe.name: webAppComponentRuntimeFilterDispatchedRequestsEnabled
webAppComponentRuntimeFilterDispatchedRe.description: Indicates whether the dispatched requests are filtered as configured in weblogic.xml.

webAppComponentRuntimeLogFilename.name: webAppComponentRuntimeLogFilename
webAppComponentRuntimeLogFilename.description: Returns the log filename as configured in the 'logging/log-filename' element in weblogic.xml

webAppComponentRuntimeSessionCookiePath.name: webAppComponentRuntimeSessionCookiePath
webAppComponentRuntimeSessionCookiePath.description: Provides the path name to which clients send cookies.

webAppComponentRuntimeJSPKeepGenerated.name: webAppComponentRuntimeJSPKeepGenerated
webAppComponentRuntimeJSPKeepGenerated.description: Provides the jsp's KeepGenerated parameter value as it is configured in weblogic.xml.

webAppComponentRuntimeSessionCookieComme.name: webAppComponentRuntimeSessionCookieComment
webAppComponentRuntimeSessionCookieComme.description: By default, all applications on WebLogic Server specify 'WebLogic Session Tracking Cookie' as the cookie comment. To provide a more specific comment, edit your application's weblogic.xml deployment descriptor.

webAppComponentRuntimeJSPCompileCommand.name: webAppComponentRuntimeJSPCompileCommand
webAppComponentRuntimeJSPCompileCommand.description: Provides the jsp's compileCommand as it is configured in weblogic.xml.

webAppComponentRuntimeJSPPageCheckSecs.name: webAppComponentRuntimeJSPPageCheckSecs
webAppComponentRuntimeJSPPageCheckSecs.description: Provides the jsp's PageCheckSecs as it is configured in weblogic.xml.

webAppComponentRuntimeContextRoot.name: webAppComponentRuntimeContextRoot
webAppComponentRuntimeContextRoot.description: Returns the context root (context path) for the webapp

webAppComponentRuntimeModuleURI.name: webAppComponentRuntimeModuleURI
webAppComponentRuntimeModuleURI.description: Returns the web-uri as configured in application.xml for the webapp. For a standalone war it will return the docroot (if exploded) or name of the war file (if archived).

webAppComponentRuntimeSessionInvalidatio.name: webAppComponentRuntimeSessionInvalidationIntervalSecs
webAppComponentRuntimeSessionInvalidatio.description: Provides the invalidation check timer interval configured for http sessions.

webAppComponentRuntimeServletReloadCheck.name: webAppComponentRuntimeServletReloadCheckSecs
webAppComponentRuntimeServletReloadCheck.description: Provides the servlet reload check seconds as it is configured in weblogic.xml.

webAppComponentRuntimeSessionCookieMaxAg.name: webAppComponentRuntimeSessionCookieMaxAgeSecs
webAppComponentRuntimeSessionCookieMaxAg.description: Provides the life span of the session cookie, in seconds, after which it expires on the client. If the value is 0, the cookie expires immediately. If set to -1, the cookie expires when the user exits the browser.

webAppComponentRuntimeSessionTimeoutSecs.name: webAppComponentRuntimeSessionTimeoutSecs
webAppComponentRuntimeSessionTimeoutSecs.description: Provides the timeout configured for http sessions.

webAppComponentRuntimeSessionIDLength.name: webAppComponentRuntimeSessionIDLength
webAppComponentRuntimeSessionIDLength.description: Provides the session ID length configured for http sessions.

webAppComponentRuntimeDeploymentState.name: webAppComponentRuntimeDeploymentState
webAppComponentRuntimeDeploymentState.description: The current deployment state of the module.

webAppComponentRuntimeSessionMonitoringE.name: webAppComponentRuntimeSessionMonitoringEnabled
webAppComponentRuntimeSessionMonitoringE.description: Provides the session monitoring indicator as it is configured in weblogic.xml.

applicationTable.name: applicationTable
applicationTable.description: An application represents a J2EE application contained in a EAR file or EAR directory. The EAR file contains a set of components such as WAR, EJB and JMS JAR components, each of which can be deployed on one or more Roles. A Role is a set of server, with a server serving more than one Role. For example a Role may be the whole Domain, a set of servers that implement the role, or a specific server. These components might include EJBs, servlets, JMS destinations, WebLogic startup and shutdown classes.

applicationIndex.description: Unique value directed from ObjectName which is used as table index

applicationParent.description: BEA-proprietary Parent object's identification, with syntax <type>:<name>

applicationDeployed.description: A boolean value (true Or false). Returns whether or not this application is deployed.

applicationComponents.description: The components that make up this application.

applicationApplicationDescriptor.description: The descriptor mbean for the application.

applicationPath.description: The path pointing to the application's EAR file. The file is relative to the Admin Server's file system.

applicationAltDescriptorPath.name: applicationAltDescriptorPath
applicationAltDescriptorPath.description: Defines a path on the filesystem for the application descriptor for this application

applicationAltWLSDescriptorPath.name: applicationAltWLSDescriptorPath
applicationAltWLSDescriptorPath.description: Defines a path on the filesystem for the WLS-specific application descriptor for this application.

applicationDeploymentTimeout.description: Milliseconds granted for a cluster deployment task on this application.

applicationDeploymentType.name: applicationDeploymentType
applicationDeploymentType.description: Specifies the category of this application.

applicationLoadOrder.description: Specifies the order applications are loaded at server startup.

applicationStagingMode.description: Indicates whether this application is being staged.

applicationStagingPath.name: applicationStagingPath
applicationStagingPath.description: Identifies the directory path on the managed server relative to the server's StagingDirectoryName.

applicationTwoPhase.name: applicationTwoPhase
applicationTwoPhase.description: Indicates whether this application is deployed using the 2 phase deployment.

bridgeDestinationCommonParent.description: BEA-proprietary Parent object's identification, with syntax <type>:<name>

clusterTable.name: clusterTable
clusterTable.description: This table represents a cluster in the domain. Servers join a cluster by calling ServerMBean.setCluster with the logical name of the cluster. A configuration may define zero or more clusters. They may be looked up by logical name.

clusterIndex.name: clusterIndex
clusterIndex.description: Unique value directed from ObjectName which is used as table index

clusterParent.name: clusterParent
clusterParent.description: BEA-proprietary Parent object's identification, with syntax <type>:<name>

clusterServers.name: clusterServers
clusterServers.description: The servers which have declared membership in this cluster.

clusterClusterAddress.name: clusterClusterAddress
clusterClusterAddress.description: The address to be used by clients to connect to this cluster. This address may be either a DNS host name that maps to multiple IP addresses or a comma separated list of single address host names or IP addresses.

clusterMulticastAddress.name: clusterMulticastAddress
clusterMulticastAddress.description: The multicast address used by cluster members to communicate with each other.

clusterMulticastTTL.name: clusterMulticastTTL
clusterMulticastTTL.description: The number of network hops that a cluster multicast message is allowed to travel. 1 restricts the cluster to one subnet. The minimum value is 1 and the maximum value is 255, inclusive.

clusterMulticastSendDelay.name: clusterMulticastSendDelay
clusterMulticastSendDelay.description: The number of milliseconds to delay sending message fragments over multicast in order to avoid OS-level buffer overflow. The default should be fine in most cases, but it may need to be tuned for odd configurations.

clusterDefaultLoadAlgorithm.name: clusterDefaultLoadAlgorithm
clusterDefaultLoadAlgorithm.description: The algorithm to be used for load-balancing between replicated services if none is specified for a particular service.

clusterServiceAgeThresholdSeconds.name: clusterServiceAgeThresholdSeconds
clusterServiceAgeThresholdSeconds.description: he number of seconds by which the age of two conflicting services must differ before one is considered older than the other.

clusterMulticastBufferSize.name: clusterMulticastBufferSize
clusterMulticastBufferSize.description: Returns the multicast socket send/receive buffer size.

clusterMulticastPort.name: clusterMulticastPort
clusterMulticastPort.description: Defines the multicast port used by cluster members to communicate with each other.

clusterClientCertProxyEnabled.name: clusterClientCertProxyEnabled
clusterClientCertProxyEnabled.description: Gets the clientCertProxyEnabled attribute of the ClusterMBean object

clusterWeblogicPluginEnabled.name: clusterWeblogicPluginEnabled
clusterWeblogicPluginEnabled.description: Gets the weblogicPluginEnabled attribute of the ClusterMBean object

clusterHealthCheckIntervalMillis.name: clusterHealthCheckIntervalMillis
clusterHealthCheckIntervalMillis.description: Interval in milliseconds at which Migratable Servers and Cluster Masters prove their liveness via the database.

clusterHealthCheckPeriodsUntilFencing.name: clusterHealthCheckPeriodsUntilFencing
clusterHealthCheckPeriodsUntilFencing.description: Maximum number of periods that a cluster member will wait before timing out a Cluster Master and also the maximum number of periods the Cluster Master will wait before timing out a Migratable Server.

clusterSessionFlushInterval.name: clusterSessionFlushInterval
clusterSessionFlushInterval.description: Interval in seconds until HTTP Sessions are periodically flushed to the backup cluster to dump session state on disk.

clusterAdditionalAutoMigrationAttempts.name: clusterAdditionalAutoMigrationAttempts
clusterAdditionalAutoMigrationAttempts.description: A migratable server could fail to come up on every possible configured machine. This attribute controls how many further attempts, after the first one, should be tried. Note that each attempt specified here indicates another full circut of migrations amongst all the configured machines. So for a 3-server cluster, and the default value of 3, a total of 9 migrations will be attempted. If it is set to -1, migrations will go on forever until the server starts.

clusterRemoteClusterAddress.name: clusterRemoteClusterAddress
clusterRemoteClusterAddress.description: Set the foreign cluster. Cluster infrastructure uses this address to connect to foreign cluster for HTTP Session WAN/MAN failover.

clusterFrontendHTTPPort.name: clusterFrontendHTTPPort
clusterFrontendHTTPPort.description: The name of the HTTP port to which all redirected URLs will be sent. Sets the FrontendHTTPPort for the default webserver (not virtual hosts) for all the servers in the cluster. Provides a method to ensure that the webapp will always have the correct PORT information, even when the request is coming through a firewall or a proxy. If this parameter is configured, the HOST header will be ignored and the information in this parameter will be used in its place, when constructing the absolute urls for redirects.

clusterMulticastDataEncryption.name: clusterMulticastDataEncryption
clusterMulticastDataEncryption.description: Enables multicast data to be incrypted. Only the multicast data is encrypted. Multicast header information is not encrypted.

clusterSecureReplicationEnabled.name: clusterSecureReplicationEnabled
clusterSecureReplicationEnabled.description: Servers in a cluster replicates session data. If replication channel is defined then the session data will be sent using the replication channel protocol and secured replication settings will be ignored. If no replication channel is defined and secured replication is enabled then session data for in-memory replication will be sent over SSL using default secured channel. However, this added security for replication traffic comes with a significant cluster performance degradation. It should only be enabled if security is of greater concern than the performance degradation.

clusterJobSchedulerTableName.name: clusterJobSchedulerTableName
clusterJobSchedulerTableName.description: The table name to use for storing timers active with the job scheduler

clusterReplicationTimeoutEnabled.name: clusterReplicationTimeoutEnabled
clusterReplicationTimeoutEnabled.description: Indicates if timeout should be applied to session replication calls.

clusterAsyncSessionQueueTimeout.name: clusterAsyncSessionQueueTimeout
clusterAsyncSessionQueueTimeout.description: Interval in seconds until the producer thread will wait for the AsyncSessionQueue to become unblocked. Should be similar to the RequestTimeOut as that will determine the longest that the queue should remain full.

clusterInterClusterCommLinkHealthCheckIn.name: clusterInterClusterCommLinkHealthCheckInterval
clusterInterClusterCommLinkHealthCheckIn.description: If the cluster link between two clusters goes down, a trigger will run to periodically to see if the link is restored. The duration is specified in milliseconds.

clusterSessionFlushThreshold.name: clusterSessionFlushThreshold
clusterSessionFlushThreshold.description: When number of sessions to be flushed reaches this threshold limit, sessions will be flushed to the backup cluster before the flush interval. This helps the server to flush sessions faster under load.

clusterClusterType.name: clusterClusterType
clusterClusterType.description: Optimizes cross-cluster replication for the type of network that servers in the clusters use for administrative communication. To enhance the reliability of HTTP sessions, you can configure servers in one cluster to replicate the session data to servers in a different cluster. In such an environment, configure the clusters to be one of the following types: man if the clustered servers can send their data through a metro area network (man) in which latency is negligible. With this ClusterType value, servers replicate session state synchronously and in memory only. For example, when serverA in cluster1 starts an HTTP session, its backup server, serverB in cluster2, immediately replicates this session in memory to Server B. wan if the clusters are far apart or send their data through a wide area network (wan) that experiences significant network latency. With this ClusterType value, a server replicates session state synchronously to the backup server in the same cluster and asynchronously to a server in the remote cluster. For example, when serverA in cluster1 starts an HTTP session, it sends the data to serverB in cluster1 and then asynchronously sends data to serverX in cluster 2. ServerX will persist the session state in the database. If you persist session data in a replicating database, and if you prefer to use the database to replicate the data instead of WebLogic Server, choose a cluster type of wan and leave the remote cluster address undefined. WebLogic Server saves the session data to the local database and assumes that the database replicates data as needed.

clusterGreedySessionFlushInterval.name: clusterGreedySessionFlushInterval
clusterGreedySessionFlushInterval.description: Interval in seconds until HTTP Sessions are periodically flushed to secondary server.

clusterPersistSessionsOnShutdown.name: clusterPersistSessionsOnShutdown
clusterPersistSessionsOnShutdown.description: When shutting down servers, sessions are not updated. If the primary and secondary servers of a session are shut down with no session updates, the session will be lost. Turning on PersistSessionsOnShutdown will save any active sessions to the database specified in {@link ClusterMBean#getDataSourceForSessionPersistence()} when a server is shutdown. The sessions will not be written at any other time. (For example, they are not saved via this mechanism if there is a server crash.) This attribute is applicable both to session persistence on server shutdown or session persistence across a WAN. Rolling upgrade can potential have a bad interaction with traditional in-memory session replication. As managed servers are shutdown and upgraded, in-memory servlet sessions will be lost if both primary and secondary are rebooted before a new request arrives for the session.

clusterMigrationBasis.name: clusterMigrationBasis
clusterMigrationBasis.description: Controls the mechanism used for server migration.

clusterReplicationChannel.name: clusterReplicationChannel
clusterReplicationChannel.description: The channel name to be used for replication traffic. Cluster infrastructure uses this channel to send updates for HTTP sessions and stateful session beans. If none is set then the default channel will be used. In order for this feature to work, the named channel must exist on all members of the cluster and must be configured to use the same protocol. It is valid for the selected channel to be configured to use a secure protocol.

clusterFencingGracePeriodMillis.name: clusterFencingGracePeriodMillis
clusterFencingGracePeriodMillis.description: During automatic migration, if the Cluster Master determines a server to be dead, it waits for this period of time (in milliseconds) before the Cluster Master migrates the service to another server in the cluster.

clusterFrontendHost.name: clusterFrontendHost
clusterFrontendHost.description: The name of the host to which all redirected URLs will be sent. Sets the HTTP FrontendHost for the default webserver (not virtual hosts) for all the servers in the cluster. Provides a method to ensure that the webapp will always have the correct HOST information, even when the request is coming through a firewall or a proxy. If this parameter is configured, the HOST header will be ignored and the information in this parameter will be used in its place, when constructing the absolute urls for redirects.

clusterMemberWarmupTimeoutSeconds.name: clusterMemberWarmupTimeoutSeconds
clusterMemberWarmupTimeoutSeconds.description: Maximum number of seconds that a cluster member will wait to discover and synchronize with other servers in the cluster. Normally, the member will be able to sync in 30 seconds. If the value of this attribute is higher, that does not necessarily mean that it will take longer for the member to warmup. Instead it defines an upper bound on the time that a server will wait to sync with the servers that it has discoverred. If the value is set 0, servers will not attempt to discover other running server in the cluster during server initialization

clusterFrontendHTTPSPort.name: clusterFrontendHTTPSPort
clusterFrontendHTTPSPort.description: The name of the secure HTTP port to which all redirected URLs will be sent. Sets the FrontendHTTPSPort for the default webserver (not virtual hosts) for all the servers in the cluster. Provides a method to ensure that the webapp will always have the correct PORT information, even when the request is coming through a firewall or a proxy. If this parameter is configured, the HOST header will be ignored and the information in this parameter will be used in its place, when constructing the absolute urls for redirects.

clusterClusterBroadcastChannel.name: clusterClusterBroadcastChannel
clusterClusterBroadcastChannel.description: Specifies the channel used to handle communications within a cluster. If no channel is specified the default channel is used. ClusterBroadcastChannel is only are supported if the unicast messaging type is used.

clusterIdlePeriodsUntilTimeout.name: clusterIdlePeriodsUntilTimeout
clusterIdlePeriodsUntilTimeout.description: Maximum number of periods that a cluster member will wait before timing out a member of a cluster. Maximum number of periods that a cluster member will wait before timing out a member of a cluster.

clusterNumberOfServersInClusterAddress.name: clusterNumberOfServersInClusterAddress
clusterNumberOfServersInClusterAddress.description: Number of servers to be listed from this cluster when generating a cluster address automatically. This setting has no effect if Cluster Address is explicitly set.

clusterClusterMessagingMode.name: clusterClusterMessagingMode
clusterClusterMessagingMode.description: Specifies the messaging type used in the cluster. Multicast messaging, the default, is provided for backwards compatibility. Unicast message is recommended for new clusters.

clusterMillisToSleepBetweenAutoMigration.name: clusterMillisToSleepBetweenAutoMigrationAttempts
clusterMillisToSleepBetweenAutoMigration.description: Controls how long of a pause there should be between the migration attempts described in getAdditionalAutoMigrationAttempts(). Note that this delay only happens when the server has failed to come up on every machine.

clusterAutoMigrationTableName.name: clusterAutoMigrationTableName
clusterAutoMigrationTableName.description: Return the name of the table to be used for server migration.

clusterWANSessionPersistenceTableName.name: clusterWANSessionPersistenceTableName
clusterWANSessionPersistenceTableName.description: Return the name of the table to be used for WAN session persistence.

comApartmentThreaded.description: Controls the flag that is used to initialize COM in native mode. * By default, jCOM initializes COM using the COINIT_MULTITHREADED_FLAG. * If the server logs a Class Not Registered Message when using native mode, * try setting this property. (COINIT_APARTMENTTHREADED).

comNativeModeEnabled.name: comNativeModeEnabled
comNativeModeEnabled.description: Use native DLLs to allow Java objects to interact with COM Objects.

comPrefetchEnums.description: Some COM methods return a COM VariantEnumeration type. The java2com tool * automatically converts the returned type into a java.lang.Enumeration. * This is not a perfect match since COM enumerations have no equivalent * to the hasMoreElements() call. The client must continue to * call nextElement until a NoSuchElementException * occurs.

domainJTA.description: Return the JTA configuration for this Domain.

domainLog.description: Return the domain logfile configuration for this domain.

domainSNMPAgent.description: SNMPAgentMBean is a singleton MBean describing SNMP Agent configuration details. This MBean has getters and setters for other SNMP related configuration MBeans.

domainConfigurationVersion.description: The release identifier for the configuration.

domainConsoleContextPath.description: Specifies the context path for the WLS console.

domainAdministrationPortEnabled.name: domainAdministrationPortEnabled
domainAdministrationPortEnabled.description: Indicates whether or not the administration port should be enabled for the domain.

domainClusterConstraintsEnabled.name: domainClusterConstraintsEnabled
domainClusterConstraintsEnabled.description: Retrieves the attribute indicating whether strict cluster constraints are enforced or not for this domain.

domainConsoleEnabled.name: domainConsoleEnabled
domainConsoleEnabled.description: Indicates whether the WLS console should be auto-deployed for this domain.

domainInternalAppsDeployOnDemandEnabled.name: domainInternalAppsDeployOnDemandEnabled
domainInternalAppsDeployOnDemandEnabled.description: Specifies whether internal applications such as the console, uddi, wlstestclient, and uddiexplorer are deployed on demand (first access) instead of during server startup.

domainDomainVersion.name: domainDomainVersion
domainDomainVersion.description: Defines the common version of all servers in a domain. In a domain containing servers that are not all at the same release version, this attribute is used to determine the feature level that servers will assume. The value must be less than or equal to the version of any managed server in the domain. If this value is not equal to the version of the release version of the admin server, then the admin server will not be allowed to make modifications to the configuration.

domainConfigBackupEnabled.name: domainConfigBackupEnabled
domainConfigBackupEnabled.description: If true, then backups of the configuration will be made during server boot.

domainConsoleExtensionDirectory.name: domainConsoleExtensionDirectory
domainConsoleExtensionDirectory.description: Returns the directory path that console extensions are loaded from.

domainConfigurationAuditType.name: domainConfigurationAuditType
domainConfigurationAuditType.description: Returns the criteria used for auditing configuration events (configuration changes and other operations): CONFIG_CHANGE_NONE Configuration events will neither be written to the server log or directed to the Security Audit Framework. CONFIG_CHANGE_LOG Configuration events will be written to the server log. CONFIG_CHANGE_AUDITConfiguration events will be directed to the Security Audit Framework. CONFIG_CHANGE_LOG_AND_AUDIT Configuration events will be written to the server log and directed to the Security Audit Framework.

domainAdministrationProtocol.name: domainAdministrationProtocol
domainAdministrationProtocol.description: The default protocol for communicating through the administration port or administration channels. (Requires you to enable the administration port or to create an administration channel.) If requests through the administration port or an administration channel do not specify a protocol, WebLogic Server uses the protocol specified here.

domainProductionModeEnabled.name: domainProductionModeEnabled
domainProductionModeEnabled.description: Specifies whether all servers in this domain run in production mode. You can configure servers in your domain to start in one of two modes, development or production. You use development mode while you are developing your applications. Development mode uses a relaxed security configuration and enables you to auto-deploy applications. You use production mode when your application is running in its final form. A production domain uses full security and may use clusters or other advanced features. The runtime mode is a domain-wide setting. As each Managed Server starts, it refers to the mode of the Administration Server to determine its runtime mode. If you configure the domain to run in production mode, the Administration Server saves this setting to the domains configuration document.

ejbContainerJavaCompilerPreClassPath.description: Return the options to prepend to the Java compiler classpath for when we need to compile Java code.

ejbContainerKeepGenerated.description: Return the options to prepend to the Java compiler classpath for when we need to compile Java code.

executeQueueParent.description: BEA-proprietary Parent object's identification, with syntax <type>:<name>

executeQueueThreadCount.description: The number of threads assigned to this queue.

executeQueueThreadsMaximum.description: Returns the maximum number of threads in the pool.

executeQueueQueueLengthThresholdPercent.name: executeQueueQueueLengthThresholdPercent
executeQueueQueueLengthThresholdPercent.description: The percentage of the Queue Length size that can be reached before this server indicates an overflow condition for the queue. If the overflow condition is reached and the current thread count has not reached the ThreadsMaximum value, then ThreadsIncrease number of threads are added.

executeQueueThreadsIncrease.name: executeQueueThreadsIncrease
executeQueueThreadsIncrease.description: Specifies the number of threads to increase the queue length when the queue length theshold is reached. This threshold is determined by the QueueLengthThresholdPercent value. The following consideration applies to the dynamic nature of ThreadsMaximum and ThreadsIncrease attributes. If any of these attributes change during runtime, the changed value comes into effect when the next request is submitted to the execute queue and the scheduler decides to increase threads depending on the queue threshold conditions.

executeQueueThreadsMinimum.name: executeQueueThreadsMinimum
executeQueueThreadsMinimum.description: The minimum number of threads that WebLogic Server will maintain in the queue.

executeQueueQueueLength.name: executeQueueQueueLength
executeQueueQueueLength.description: The maximum number of simultaneous requests that this server can hold in the queue.

iiopIndex.description: Unique value directed from ObjectName which is used as table index

iiopParent.name: iiopParent
iiopParent.description: BEA-proprietary Parent object's identification, with syntax <type>:<name>

iiopCompleteMessageTimeout.name: iiopCompleteMessageTimeout
iiopCompleteMessageTimeout.description: Specify the maximum number of seconds spent * waiting for a complete IIOP message to be received. * This attribute helps guard against denial of * service attacks in which a caller indicates that * they will be sending a message of a certain size * which they never finish sending.

iiopIdleConnectionTimeout.name: iiopIdleConnectionTimeout
iiopIdleConnectionTimeout.description: Specify the maximum number of seconds an IIOP connection is * allowed to be idle before it is closed by the server. This * attribute helps guard against server deadlock through too many * open connections.

iiopMaxMessageSize.name: iiopMaxMessageSize
iiopMaxMessageSize.description: Specify the maximum IIOP message size allowable in a message header. * This attribute attempts to prevent a denial of service attack whereby * a caller attempts to force the server to allocate more memory than * is available thereby keeping the server from responding quickly to * other requests.

iiopDefaultCharCodeset.name: iiopDefaultCharCodeset
iiopDefaultCharCodeset.description: Specify what codeset should be used for the default native character codeset.

iiopDefaultMinorVersion.name: iiopDefaultMinorVersion
iiopDefaultMinorVersion.description: Specify the default minor GIOP version for IIOP messages.

iiopDefaultWideCharCodeset.name: iiopDefaultWideCharCodeset
iiopDefaultWideCharCodeset.description: Specify what codeset should be used for the default native wide character codeset.

iiopTxMechanism.name: iiopTxMechanism
iiopTxMechanism.description: Specify whether IIOP should use the WebLogic-specific JTA to propagate transactions or the OMG-specified OTS.

iiopUseStatefulAuthentication.name: iiopUseStatefulAuthentication
iiopUseStatefulAuthentication.description: Specify whether to advertise RMI objects and EJBs as supporting stateful CSIv2. Stateful CSIv2 is more efficient than stateless, requiring only a single authentication step for each remote principal. Stateless CSIv2 requires per-request authentication. Stateful CSIv2 is not required by J2EE 1.3 and so some ORBs do not support it. Stateful CSIv2 is enabled by default. This property can be changed at the object-level by changing the object's <stateful-authentication> runtime descriptor property.

iiopUseJavaSerialization.name: iiopUseJavaSerialization
iiopUseJavaSerialization.description: Specity whether to use java serialization for marshalling objects. Setting this property improves performance when marshalling objects with very large object graphs.

iiopUseFullRepositoryIdList.name: iiopUseFullRepositoryIdList
iiopUseFullRepositoryIdList.description: Specify whether to use full Repository ID lists when sending value type information for custom-marshaled types. Full Repository ID lists allow C++ ORBS to truncate values to base types. For RMI-IIOP and Java ORBs doing this merely increases transmission overhead. JDK ORBs are known to have problems with these so setting this will prevent JDK ORB access from working.

iiopEnableIORServlet.name: iiopEnableIORServlet
iiopEnableIORServlet.description: Enable getior servlet used to publish COS Naming Service IORs

iiopSystemSecurity.name: iiopSystemSecurity
iiopSystemSecurity.description: Specify the value System Security. The following variables are affected. clientCertAuthentication, clientAuthentication, identityAssertion confidentiality, integrity. The value set in this MBean would only be picked up if the value set in RTD.xml is 'config'.

iiopUseSerialFormatVersion2.name: iiopUseSerialFormatVersion2
iiopUseSerialFormatVersion2.description: Specify whether to advertise RMI objects and EJBs as supporting RMI-IIOP serial format version 2 for custom marshaled objects.

jmsBridgeDestinationAdapterJNDIName.name: jmsBridgeDestinationAdapterJNDIName
jmsBridgeDestinationAdapterJNDIName.description: The JNDI name of the adapter used to communicate with the specified destination. This name is specified in the adapter's deployment descriptor file and is used by the WebLogic Server Connector container to bind the adapter in WebLogic Server JNDI.

jmsBridgeDestinationClasspath.name: jmsBridgeDestinationClasspath
jmsBridgeDestinationClasspath.description: The CLASSPATH of the bridge destination. Used mainly to connect to another release of WebLogic Server. When connecting to a destination that is running on WebLogic Server 6.0 or earlier, the bridge destination must supply a CLASSPATH that indicates the locations of the classes for the earlier WebLogic Server implementation. When connecting to a third-party JMS product, the bridge destination must supply the product's CLASSPATH in the WebLogic Server CLASSPATH.

jmsBridgeDestinationUserName.name: jmsBridgeDestinationUserName
jmsBridgeDestinationUserName.description: The optional user name the adapter uses to access the bridge destination. All operations on the specified destination are done using this user name and the corresponding password. Therefore, the User Name/Password for the source and target destinations must have permission to the access the underlying destinations in order for the messaging bridge to work.
